added.title: Power Moves
added.description: When Robin starts doing power moves with Cyborg, Beast Boy gets very jealous.

added.title: Little Buddies
added.description: Cyborg wants Pain Bot to be his "little buddy" but is the destructive robot too dangerous to be a sidekick?

added.title: Grandma Voice
added.description: In order to defeat Mother Mae Eye, Cyborg starts using a grandma voice but soon that persona takes over and he begins making the other Titans dress warmly and clean their dishes.

added.title: The Return of Slade
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg insist on hiring a clown for a Titans party, even though Robin tells them that clowns are for little kids. When the clown fails to live up to their memories, Cyborg and Beast Boy decide to give the clown some cool updates.

added.title: Forest Pirates
added.description: The Titans are at Super Hero Summer Camp for the week and they may need to add another teammate to win the big canoe race.

added.title: Royal Jelly
added.description: Bumblebee offers to help Robin with his leadership skills by teaching him how to act like a queen bee.

added.title: Had to Be There
added.description: So she isn't left out of inside jokes, the Titans time travel to past adventures and insert Bumblebee into their memories.

added.title: The Viewers Decide
added.description: It's Titans West vs Titans East as the two teams compete for who gets Bumblebee.

added.title: Be Mine
added.description: Beast Boy invites Tara to the Titan's Valentine's Day dance and she accepts in order to destroy all of the Titans and exact revenge on Beast Boy.

added.title: Opposites
added.description: Cyborg has a star-crossed crush on Jinx, the cutest member of The Hive.

added.title: Love Monsters
added.description: Despite Raven's warnings, Starfire showers love on the adorable twin destroyers of the universe.

added.title: How 'Bout Some Effort
added.description: It's Valentine's Day and Cyborg goes to great lengths to make it special for his girlfriend Jinx.

added.title: BBRAE Part 1
added.description: Beast Boy writes a song to tell Raven how he feels about her.

added.title: Cheeseburger Backpack
added.description: A mission to the Lunar Sea Spire takes a treacherous turn, but Steven has packed his totally amazing Cheeseburger Backpack with anything they could ever need!

added.title: Jail Break
added.description: Steven teams up with a new ally to rescue the Gems.

added.title: Bubble Buddies
added.description: Steven looks like a hero when he forms a magic crystal bubble around himself to protect a girl he likes from danger, but then panics when he can't figure out how to turn the bubble off!

added.title: The Answer
added.description: Garnet finally tells Steven the story of how she came to be a Crystal Gem.

added.title: Love Letters
added.description: Steven and Connie help Jamie the mailman with love.

added.title: Keeping It Together
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

added.title: Steven's Dream
added.description: A strange dream prompts Steven to search for answers.

added.title: Storm in the Room
added.description: Steven goes into his room in the temple to look for answers.

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Last One Out of Beach City
added.description: Pearl, Steven and Amethyst go to a rock show.

added.title: Steven's Birthday
added.description: Steven has a birthday party out at the barn, and decides he has some growing up to do.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: Laser Light Cannon
added.description: A magical comet hurtles toward Beach City, and Steven must dig through his father's collection of old junk, and the past, to find the weapon that can save the town.

added.title: The Kiss
added.description: Gumball is traumatised when accidentally kissed on the mouth by his Grandma JoJo.

added.title: The Date
added.description: Gumball discovers the difference between a "date" and a "pet's funeral"...the hard way.

added.title: The Shell
added.description: Gumball inadvertently cracks open Penny's shell and discovers who she really is inside . . . While performing a school play, Gumball is so nervous about kissing Penny that he accidentally headbutts her and cracks open her shell. They discover that under Penny's shell is an emotional shape-shifting inner self. Penny's father is determined for Penny to keep it hidden but Gumball encourages her to show the world who, or what, she really is . . .

added.title: The Romantic
added.description: After Gumball convinces himself that Penny doesn't love him as much as she used to, he decides to put together a romantic quest to remind her of all the good times they've had together. But Gumball's romantic gesture backfires, landing Penny and maybe their relationship in serious peril.

added.title: The Love
added.description: The residents of Elmore search for the meaning of love.

added.title: The Misunderstandings
added.description: Gumball has misunderstood about his date with Penny. He thought they were meeting for dinner but they were actually meeting for lunch at a Diner called Dinner. He runs to the mall but everyone he meets on the way seems to misunderstand him in a different way. Once he finally does get to the mall, it seems all his misunderstandings have caught up with him.

added.title: The Matchmaker
added.description: Gumball catches Darwin gazing wistfully at a photo of Teri on Elmore Plus and secretly enlists Carrie to help bring them together. But when they can't make Darwin and Teri's love blossom naturally, they decide to make it happen supernaturally.

added.title: The Heart
added.description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

added.title: The Web
added.description: Gumball and Darwin realize that the adult residents of Elmore are dangerously naive when it comes to being safe online. In fact they are in serious need of the boys help with even the simplest of tasks. And no more so than their mom, Nicole.

added.title: The Decisions
added.description: When everything goes wrong in Darwin's life, he begins to suspect that Gumball's bad influence might be to blame. Darwin decides to go elsewhere for guidance and finds a new mentor in Alan. But maybe it's time Darwin started making his own decisions.

added.title: The Test
added.description: Gumball is livid when an online test keeps telling him that his character-type is "The Loser". He's convinced the only way to shake off this label is to do the opposite of everything he normally would. But Gumball suppressing his natural instincts leaves a vacuum, a Gumball-shaped hole that someone has to fill. That someone is Tobias, who starts turning the whole show into a cliched sitcom.

added.title: The Traitor
added.description: When Alan ditches Gumball to do something more fun, Gumball is desperate to track him down and make him pay for his betrayal.

added.title: The Tag
added.description: Gumball and Darwin get caught in the middle of Dad and Mr Robinson's trashcan feud.

added.title: The Tape
added.description: Gumball and Darwin fail to make some instant homemade movie classics.

added.title: The Third
added.description: Gumball and Darwin spice up their friendship by introducing a third best friend.

added.title: Meet Mumm-ra and the Mutants
added.description: The Thundercats have met their match with the evil, undead Mumm-ra! He and the bumbling Mutants have made it their goal to stop the Thundercats by any means necessary, but of course the Thundercats have other plans!

added.title: Meet Panthro
added.description: Panthro may be the strongest cat on Third Earth, but one of his biggest strengths is that he can fix anything!  And the rest of the Thundercats break enough stuff to really put his skills to the test, but it's nothing a pro like Panthro can't handle.

added.title: Meet Cheetara
added.description: Cheetara is the coolest cat around! Not only is she so fast that she can outrun lightning, but so clever she can outsmart Mumm-Ra's evil plans! Villains don't stand a chance against Cheetara…well, unless Mumm-Ra uses his Doom Staff, then she might be in trouble.

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: Panda's Date
added.description: When a vendor at the Farmer's Market (LUCY) sticks Panda with an EpiPen reviving him after an allergic reaction, Panda comes to in the arms of his dream girl. Panda tries to woo this woman of his dreams but his brothers and his own insecurities get in the way.

added.title: Bear Flu
added.description: The Bears become terribly ill and Chloe takes it upon herself to take care of them. But things get tricky when word of the Bears' sickness goes viral.

added.title: The Audition
added.description: The Bears audition to be the next mascot for their favorite cereal. They get so caught up in the process that their competitiveness gets the best of them.

added.title: Captain Craboo
added.description: The Bears are reunited with their pet crab, Captain Craboo. But after an unfortunate run-in with Nom Nom, the Bears may lose their pet forever.

added.title: Baby Bears on a Plane
added.description: The Baby Bears have an adventure in the sky while aboard a plane to Sweden. But when the baby Bears are forced to sit in different sections of the plan, things get a bit haywire for everyone on board.

added.title: Yuri and the Bear
added.description: Baby Ice Bear lives alone in the arctic and meets a mysterious man named Yuri. Together they help each other survive the cold environment.

added.title: Grizzly the Movie
added.description: Grizz gets cast in a movie about a Grizzly Bear! But Grizz soon realizes the movie's depiction of grizzly bears is not what he had in mind.

added.title: Pet Shop
added.description: Pet Shop tells the tale of where the Baby Bears once lived, and after a run-in with a video crew shooting a Sarah McLachlan-type animal adoption video, almost seized an opportunity to find a home separated from each other.

added.title: Bobbie Blobby
added.description: Action Axel tells us all about Bobbie Blobby.

added.title: Boo
added.description: Galileo thinks it's funny to play tricks on the Power Players, but how will they react?

added.title: Emergency
added.description: Slobot arrives looking panicked while Sarge Charge is training: it's Axel!

added.title: Ride'em
added.description: One by one, the beaten up Power Players go and ask Slobot to fix them. What's going on?

added.title: Sarge Charge
added.description: Sarge Charge tells tales from the battlefield…from a toy's perspective!

added.title: A Titans Showdown
added.description: The Power Players clash in Masko's ring... in a laughing contest!

added.title: Bearbarian
added.description: Action Axel tells us all about Bearbarian.

added.title: For Elite Only
added.description: Sarge gets Action Axel ready for an elite mission...he's just not sure which mission!

added.title: Zoe
added.description: Action Axel tells us all about Zoe.

added.title: Make Over
added.description: Bearbarian asks Slobot to dye his fur a different color.

added.title: Madcap
added.description: Action Axel and Galileo tell us all about...Madcap!

added.title: Galileo
added.description: Action Axel tells us all about Galileo.

added.title: Second First Date
added.description: Love is in the air and Cupid arrives to resolve romantic tension around the plaza.

added.title: Rad Likes Robots
added.description: Rad finds love in an unexpected place.

added.title: The Perfect Meal
added.description: KO teams up with Beardo to make the perfect meal for Carol.

added.title: My Fair Carol
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up to help Carol out with a special occasion.

added.title: KO, Rad, and Enid!
added.description: When confronted with their lack of a team gimmick, KO, Rad, and Enid wonder what their group identity should be.

added.title: Chip's Damage
added.description: Elodie enlists KO to help figure out what to do about Chip Damage.

added.title: K.O. vs Fink
added.description: When Fink taunts KO for being a momma's boy, he grapples with newfound insecurity about it.

added.title: Bittersweet Rivals
added.description: Enid is forced to confront lingering issues from a past friendship.

added.title: All in the Villainy
added.description: KO, Rad and Enid are confused to find the villains are more interested in battling each other than them.

added.title: I Am Jethro
added.description: When a different kind of Jethro rolls off the assembly line, the plaza is in for some surprises.

added.title: Beach Episode
added.description: Surf's up on a wacky beach adventure when our heroes are challenged to the ultimate beach battle.

added.title: Dark Plaza
added.description: KO and the heroes of the Plaza fight to save Lakewood Plaza Turbo with everything on the line.

added.title: Legends of Mr. Gar
added.description: Rad and Enid reminisce about when they started working at the bodega and learned how amazing Mr. Gar really is.

added.title: Everybody Likes Rad?
added.description: When Rad posts a video that goes viral, he tries to milk his 15 minutes of fame.

added.title: Let's Have a Stakeout
added.description: KO joins Mr. Gar on a stakeout.

added.title: Two Swords
added.description: Finn and Jake contend with a mysterious, but familiar, new being.

added.title: Gary's Synthesizer
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby unplug some cables in an old synthesizer. They have to travel to the planet of Synthos in order to re-connect them and bring Gary back to life.

added.title: Garage Door
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to fix the garage door.

added.title: Maestros
added.description: Cuando Darwin les pregunta a sus amigos qué profesor merece estar en la portada del anuario, iles cuesta encontrar a un solo candidato digno!
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Carrie
added.description: Darwin se propone encontrar una foto de Carrie para la portada del anuario escolar, pero ambos terminan recordando todas sus travesuras espeluznantes del pasado.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Banana Joe
added.description: Cuando el director Brown le asigna a Darwin la tarea de hacer el anuario escolar, Darwin comienza pidiéndole a Banana Joe, el payaso de la clase, una simple selfi para la portada. Pero con Banana Joe, las cosas nunca son tan simples.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Seed No Evil/City of Clipsville
added.description: Seed No Evil: When a prehistoric caveman thaws out in Townsville, the girls must stop him from stealing the Mayor's seeds./City of Clipsville: The girls reminisce on their adventures in these new, never-before-seen clips!

added.title: Prime Mates/Coupe D'Etat
added.description: Prime Mates: Back when Mojo Jojo tried to take over the world with primates, there was one monkey who didn't get his due: Mopey Popo. Now, Mopey is back to try and be just as evil as Mojo intended./Coupe D'Etat: When the Professor tricks out his car, the girls realize that this K.A.R.R. is taking the Professor away from them both figuratively and literally.

added.title: Gold Watch
added.description: Benson has to get to work on time so he can win a gold watch.

added.title: Too Old
added.description: Finn, Jake and PB discover a talented mutant named Lemonsqueak at The Pageant of Mutants. Now they must find a way to free him from the lemongrabs.

added.title: Ready to Rumble
added.description: After Ben thinks he's broken Gwen's computer, he sneaks off and enters an "ultimate wrestling competition" to win enough money to buy her a new one. On the mat as Fourarms, he becomes an instant celebrity hit with the fans and ends up going up against a tandem of odd looking brothers with special mutant-like powers. Initially adversaries, Ben and the brothers become allies when Ben discovers the brothers are beholden to a powerful mob boss. Ben helps the brothers defeat the mob boss and his henchmen, and in the end realizes Gwen's computer was never really broken.

added.title: Brebre Parte 1
added.description: Chico Bestia escribe una canción para contarle a Raven lo que siente por ella.

added.title: Ben 10 vs. Negative 10 Part 2
added.description: Ben, Max and Gwen put up an Alamo like stand inside the bunker at Mount Rushmore and against great odds take down the Forever King's band of baddies. In the end, Ben goes Upchuck and digests the powerful energy source, preventing the Forever King from using it for nefarious purposes. However this ultimate baddie is able to disappear...perhaps to return once again.

added.title: Uncle Cupid
added.description: Cupid, too lonely to perform his Valentine's Day duties, comes to Uncle Grandpa for help.

added.title: Not So Secret Service
added.description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

added.title: Too Young
added.description: Princess Bubblegum's uncle attempts to usurp Ooo's throne.

added.title: Benwolf
added.description: In New Mexico, Max stops to visit an old friend, who's a Navajo Chief. Suddenly, a powerful storm comes out of nowhere. And behind bolts of purple lightning, a Navajo werewolf appears. As Ben battles the werewolf, he appears to be bitten and turns into Benwolf.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: The Unnaturals
added.description: Ben learns that evil robots have replaced all the kids at the Little League World Series. And now they want to replace the President of the USA!

added.title: The Visitor
added.description: A mysterious alien named Xylene shows up and wants to return the Omnitrix to its rightful owner, Grandpa Max!

added.title: Valentimes
added.description: When Clarence notices his teacher Ms. Baker is the only one in class left without a Valentine this year, he decides to enlist the help of Sumo to set her up with Sumo's teacher, Mr. Mozer! Will sparks fly or will the boy's naïve view of romance backfire?

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Land
added.description: Pizza Steve must find a way to sneak onto his own roller coaster at the newly opened Uncle Grandpa Land.

added.title: To Cut a Woman's Hair
added.description: Finn needs to find a princess willing to give up a lock of her hair to save Jake from a balding witch.

added.title: Grave Sights
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to earn a day off, and in the process, they battle some angry zombies.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Retires
added.description: Uncle Grandpa discovers a new, unusual occupation.

added.title: Monkey Love
added.description: When Blossom makes a bad call, she becomes afraid to try again.

added.title: Bridezilla
added.description: When Mojo and Barbarus announce their wedding, the girls are convinced that they're up to no good.

added.title: Go Viral
added.description: Challenged by Muscle Man, Mordecai and Rigby want to create the most popular viral video of all time.

added.title: Pretty Great Day with a Girl
added.description: Clarence and Amy, a unique girl from down the street, bond over a hunt for a monster-sized rock called an "erratic."

added.title: Trouble in Lumpy Space
added.description: Finn and Jake try to go on a quest while protecting Tree Trunks.

added.title: Abate and Switch
added.description: When the JLA tries to stop the Brothers Djinn, the ghoulish trio are able to direct spells on our heroes by saying their names forcing them to disguise themselves as each other in order to foil the spells.

added.title: Clarence Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: When Clarence is asked out on a date by Ashley, a girl in his class, he realizes he doesn't know the first thing about having a girlfriend! Clarence enlists Sumo and Jeff to transform himself into the perfect gentleman just in time for his big date.

added.title: Biggest Fan
added.description: An obsessed super fan goes to dangerous extremes just to be saved by her Warrior heroes: Vambre and Prohyas.

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: Arrested Development
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

added.title: Field Trip
added.description: A group of teenage superheroes are being shown around the Fortress of Solitude when they inadvertently cause the phantom zone projector to trap Superman and release three Kryptonian criminals.

added.title: Ben Again
added.description: When Eon causes 11-year old Ben swap minds with teen Ben, it's up to Gwen, Rook, and Professor Paradox to set things straight.  (Featuring Eon and Professor Paradox.)

added.title: Neighborhood Grill
added.description: Clarence is so troubled by the sight of his teacher in a social setting outside of school, he can't stop himself from intruding on her doomed blind date.

added.title: Leg Wrestler
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus argue over what show to watch on TV, Pizza Steve has the perfect way to solve their dilemma: Leg wrestling battle!

added.title: Bad Man Oldman
added.description: When the Warriors re-thatch Old Man Oldman's roof and absentmindedly make it look like Prohyas' hair, Oldman dons an giant evil toupee exacts his revenge!

added.title: Battle for the Bottled City
added.description: Atom shrinks Superman so he can visit his fellow Kryptonians in the bottled city of Kandor. Soon after, Brainiac attacks and takes off with the bottle. Atom is forced to take control of one of Superman's damaged robots in order to follow after Brainiac and retrieve the city.

added.title: Action Comedy
added.description: Rhyboflaven's local fictional superhero, Broccoli Punch, has an all-new, spectacular action stage show, but when Flonk masquerades as the star, the Warriors disguise themselves as broccoli bad guys to teach the imposter a lesson!

added.title: Boo-ray for Bizarro
added.description: When the diabolical Amazo attacks the League and begins to steal their powers one-by-one, the klutzy, backwards-thinking Bizarro becomes our heroes' last hope to turn things around.

added.title: Best Day Ever
added.description: Joker frees Luthor with a mother box and forces him to spend the day together, hopping all over the world, with the Justice League hot on their trail trying to catch up.

added.title: Continue?
added.description: The Mysterious Hooded Woman hires the Warriors to retrieve the Orb of Sphericity from a temple in Galacton. The odd thing is, this temple has save points! When the Warriors are defeated, they respawn, but Vambre remembers what happened and Prohyas does not.

added.title: Docky & Buford's Decidedly Pathetic Adventure
added.description: Docky Boardman and Buford want to beef up business for the Rhyboflaven Boardwalk, but in their hunt for a new attraction, they get eaten by a mammoth-sized Ramblyboo and it's up to the Warriors to get them out!

added.title: Misfortune Cookie
added.description: After receiving an ominous fortune, Uncle Grandpa must snoop out whom among his friends is an enemy in disguise.

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: Stuck Up, Up and Away/Schoolhouse Rocked
added.description: Stuck Up, Up and Away: Bratty little Princess comes to town and wants to be a Powerpuff Girl. When she doesn't get what she wants, the girls will have to pay./Schoolhouse Rocked: The Gangreen Gang goes back to school at Pokey Oaks Kindergarten and become the school bullies. Since the girls can't fight in school, how can they stop them?

added.title: Silent Treatment/Sweet 'n' Sour
added.description: The Silent Treatment: When the girls go to see a silent movie with the Professor, they end up getting pulled into the film by an old-time villain./Sweet 'n' Sour: The girls must figure out how to beat Townsville's newest band of criminals: a group of adorable little animals.

added.title: Slave the Day/Los Dos Mojos
added.description: Slave The Day: The girls save Big Billy's life, and he is forever indebted. But how will they get this bumbling fellow out of their way so they can save the world?/Los Dos Mojos: After she gets knocked on the head, Bubbles wakes up thinking she is Mojo Jojo. What is the world going to do with two evil Mojos?

added.title: Tree of Life
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo make it their mission to climb a really tall tree before it's set to be chopped down. As they scale higher and higher their reality begins to slip away.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: The Substitute
added.description: After Ms. Baker takes an unexpected personal day, she is replaced by a substitute that has a hard time handling the unruly classroom. Soon, the school day devolves into chaos and it is up to Clarence to get Mrs. Baker back to where she belongs, the classroom.

added.title: Hoofin' It
added.description: It's time for the annual Aberdale Greased Pig Chase and everyone's excited except Clarence. He feels so bad for poor little pig Butterscotch that he takes her place in the pig chase, running from townsfolk eager to take home the prized barrel full of hot dogs!

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: While watching a TV show about dreams, Clarence dozes off and enters the whimsical dreamscape that hovers above Aberdale. Here Clarence can see other people's dreams, experiencing the subconscious of all his friends and neighbors. But when things turn nightmarish, Clarence must find a way to escape back to reality.

added.title: Nuthin' Special/Neighbor Hood
added.description: Nuthing Special: Frustrated with not knowing what her special power is, Buttercup hunts to discover what makes her special./Neighbor Hood: When everyone on Bubbles' favorite show loses their happy, Bubbles helps bring it back.

added.title: Little Miss Interprets/Night Mayor
added.description: Little Miss Interprets: When the girls hear the Professor trying to make something out of sugar, spice and everything nice, they are sure he's trying to create new little girls./Night Mayor: The Mayor keeps having the same dream over and over again but he never sees the end. Now, it's up the girls to go into the Mayor's head and solve this mystery.

added.title: Power-Noia
added.description: The girls have become paralyzed by their greatest fears. Who could be behind such an evil trick?

added.title: Members Only
added.description: When the girls try to join an all-male superhero organization, they learn that sometimes supermen aren't so super.

added.title: Moral Decay/Meet the Beat Alls
added.description: Moral Decay: When Bubbles loses a tooth, she gets a shiny coin under her pillow the next day. Buttercup sees a gold mine in the mouths of Townsville's criminal element./Meet the Beat Alls: Mojo, Him, Princess and Fuzzy band together to form the Bad Four, a criminal supergroup out to destroy the Powerpuff Girls. Everything is going great until Mojo meets Moko Jono and falls in love.

added.title: Powerprof.
added.description: The girls are so busy fighting crime that the Professor doesn't get to see them anymore. So he creates a superhero suit for himself. Unfortunately, he starts cramping their superhero style.

added.title: Mo Job/Pet Feud
added.description: Mo Job: Princess hires Mojo to devise the perfect plan to destroy the girls, who are quite shocked when they find Princess has powers equal to their own./Pet Feud: The Professor creates the perfect little pet. But there's only one catch: he can only be fed once a day. When the girls each feed him, they find that their sweet little friend has become a wild beast!

added.title: Insect Inside/Powerpuff Bluff
added.description: Insect Inside: Vile villain Roach Coach has a plan to infest Townsville with an army of cockroaches! The girls overcome their squirms to squash Roach Coach's scheme and force him to bug off./Powerpuff Bluff: Three local hoods get new identities when they find grown-up-sized Powerpuff costumes inside Townsville Jail. They terrorize Townsville while the Mayor mistakenly sends the real girls to the slammer.

added.title: In the Doghouse
added.description: Buttercup must go it alone to save her family from a kidnapping.

added.title: Lights Out!
added.description: When Bliss brings a new tech product to town, it's more powerful than imagined.

added.title: The Last Donnycorn
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn is hunted by a seemingly unstoppable foe, the Powerpuff Girls have to find a way to save him before it's too late!

added.title: Clawdad
added.description: While visiting the lake, Buttercup vows to capture a legendary uncatchable crawdad.

added.title: Mini Golf Madness
added.description: Buttercup takes her game winning mini golf ball, in spite of ominous warnings of dire consequences.

added.title: Extreme Dreams
added.description: Phibby Croax hires the Warriors for the MOST EXTREME EXPERIENCE EVER!

added.title: Forever a Fishstick
added.description: After a misfire with Fishstick Magisword, Prohyas copes with completing Warrior missions as a fish stick!

added.title: Getting Ahead
added.description: When the headless body of Omnibus knocks at their door, the Warriors use Magiswords to try to make a head they can talk to with mixed results!

added.title: Don't Read the Comments
added.description: An obsession with comments and criticisms about him on the Board of Opinions drives Prohyas nuts, affecting Warrior missions for the worse and raising Vambre's ire… I mean… concerns.

added.title: Prisoners of Love
added.description: The boys try to cool off but get trapped by the Ice King.

added.title: Ricardio the Heart Guy
added.description: Finn becomes jealous of Princes Bubblegum's new suitor.

added.title: Go With Me
added.description: Finn needs a date to the movies and must balance the contrasting advice of Jake and Marceline in wooing PB so he can see that flick!

added.title: Incendium
added.description: Jake sets Finn up with the Flame Princess - with fiery results.

added.title: Burning Low
added.description: Finn starts spending a lot of time with Flame Princess...is Princess Bubblegum jealous?
